Security has been beefed up in Maiduguri and environs as President Muhammadu Buhari is expected to visit the town to declare open the Fourth Quarter Chief of Army Staff Conference. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that this is first time the president will be gracing the quarterly chief of army staff conference since he assumed office. The quarterly conference is used to review armyâ€™s activities, including operations and exercises with a view to improve on them. The president is also expected to use occasion to address troops on the frontline in the North East and assured the people of the region of his administration determination to prosecute the counter insurgency to logical conclusion. The president expected visit is being interpreted as meal booster for officers and soldiers in the aftermath of killing of a number of soldiers at Metele in Northern Borno, by the Boko Haram terrorists group.